{
  "message": "fuzz: expand dir_operations seed corpus with 11 structured seeds\n\nAdd 11 structured corpus seeds for fuzz_dir_operations covering:\n\nBlock size variations:\n- small_block_single_add: 64-byte block with single entry\n- medium_block_multi_add: 256-byte block with 5 entries\n- large_block_htree: 1024-byte block with htree insertions\n\nOperation sequences:\n- add_remove_sequence: add 3 entries then remove 2\n- stress_remove_all: add 6 entries then remove all\n- init_only: just block initialization, no mutations\n\nEntry types and names:\n- symlink_entries: symlink file type entries\n- max_name_length: entry with 24-byte name (MAX_NAME_LEN)\n- many_small_entries: 12 single-char entries (MAX_ENTRIES)\n\nEdge cases:\n- hash_collision_attempt: entries with similar prefixes\n- hash_consistency: hash version 3 verification\n- remove_nonexistent: attempt to remove missing entry\n\nSeeds exercise different block sizes (64-1024), reserved tail\nconfigurations, hash versions (0-3), and add/remove mutation\npatterns to maximize coverage of directory operation edge cases.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
